<header id="detail-header">
	<h1>The Cat and the Canary</h1>
</header>

	<section id="film-detail-container">
		<img src="../static/images/m10.jpeg" alt="Film poster">

		<p><em>The Cat and the Canary</em> is a silent comedy horror film directed by Paul Leni, starring Laura La Plante, Forrest Stanley, Creighton Hale, and Flora Finch.</p>

		<p>Paul Kohner produced the film.</p>

		<p>
			It was released by Universal Pictures on September 9, 1927, with a runtime of 82 minutes.

			
				It made $325,550  at the box office.
				When adjusted for inflation in 2023, that's approximately equivalent to $5.6 million. Data on the film's budget could not be found.
			
		</p>

		<p>
			The film was written by Alfred A. Cohn and Walter Anthony, with Hugo Riesenfeld composing the filmâ€™s music. Gilbert Warrenton oversaw cinematography, and Martin G. Cohn helped with editing the film.
		</p>

		<p><a href="https://archive.org/details/TheCatAndTheCanary1927DVDRipSiRiUsSHaRe">View an archived version of <em>The Cat and the Canary</em>.</a></p>

		<p><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Cat_and_the_Canary_(1927_film)">View the Wikipedia entry for <em>The Cat and the Canary</em>.</a></p>

		<p><a href="../index.html">Return to the list</a> to select a different film.</p>
	</section>

